WEBVTT

00:01.126 --> 00:03.438
Hey, listen, I think you remember reverend Diddum.

00:03.473 --> 00:05.750
Well, it turns out the reverend is also a lawyer.

00:05.785 --> 00:08.234
I've decided to let him handle my divorce.

00:08.269 --> 00:09.112
Instead of targeting the

00:09.147 --> 00:10.876
ex-husband, we go after the reverend.

00:10.911 --> 00:11.588
The reverend?

00:11.623 --> 00:13.341
Three sexual harassment complaints

00:13.376 --> 00:15.060
The man has a certain weakness.

00:16.594 --> 00:18.627
Did you commit this act

00:18.662 --> 00:23.309
because he was evil or because you are?

00:23.344 --> 00:25.266
Because he was.

00:27.730 --> 00:29.571
I want Alan Shore.

00:36.870 --> 00:37.813
I'd like to know how a United

00:37.848 --> 00:39.617
States congressman could be held liable

00:39.652 --> 00:41.454
for an official act of congressional

00:41.489 --> 00:43.221
business for which he enjoys immunity?

00:43.256 --> 00:45.201
You can be held liable because you've been sued

00:45.236 --> 00:46.976
under traditional state tort law

00:47.011 --> 00:48.716
for which you enjoy no immunity.

00:50.642 --> 00:51.765
I want Denny Crane.

00:53.136 --> 00:55.951
Uh, you don't want Denny Crane.

00:55.986 --> 00:58.767
Denise is one of our top…

00:58.850 --> 01:01.218
I'm entitled to the top.

01:01.478 --> 01:03.910
Is there a reason I'm not getting Denny?

01:05.982 --> 01:07.484
Denny…

01:08.109 --> 01:09.652
Denny has, uh…

01:09.694 --> 01:10.761
Mad cow disease.

01:11.779 --> 01:13.364
I just saw him on television

01:13.448 --> 01:14.949
in Kelly Nolan's murder trial.

01:14.991 --> 01:17.243
He was at the defense table for effect, Raymond.

01:17.285 --> 01:20.395
He's not capable of any complex litigation.

01:24.751 --> 01:27.179
I knew you were there, Denny.

01:27.337 --> 01:28.796
Did you?

01:28.838 --> 01:30.965
Raymond Jacobs.

01:31.007 --> 01:34.260
You handled my first divorce 15 years ago.

01:34.594 --> 01:36.471
–My wife's name was Lois?
–I remember.

01:36.512 --> 01:38.389
Why wouldn't you? You slept with her.

01:38.431 --> 01:40.349
Only after the divorce was final.

01:40.430 --> 01:43.144
May I ask, Denny, how do you feel about gun control?

01:43.186 --> 01:44.152
For communists.

01:44.187 --> 01:45.229
What about banning assault

01:45.313 --> 01:46.673
weapons in the private sector?

01:46.708 --> 01:48.339
As soon as you say it's okay to

01:48.374 --> 01:49.670
ban assault weapons, my friend,

01:49.705 --> 01:50.932
even in the private sector,

01:50.967 --> 01:52.853
you make it easier to take guns away from hunting,

01:52.888 --> 01:54.312
then personal protection.

01:54.347 --> 01:55.649
Soon the military and the

01:55.684 --> 01:56.951
police are without firearms.

01:57.723 --> 02:00.243
By banning assault weapons in the private sector,

02:00.278 --> 02:02.763
the military and the police would lose their guns?

02:02.798 --> 02:04.067
And their dominoes.

02:04.350 --> 02:05.777
It's a whole theory.

02:07.209 --> 02:10.136
She's a Liberal. Can't even hunt.

